st_description":"Feed the pipeline a mix of valid and malformed JSON entries: (1) missing required fields, (2) invalid JSON syntax, (3) wrong data types, (4) truncated/incomplete entries, (5) null values where forbidden. Verify: (1) pipeline completes without exception, (2) all valid entries are processed correctly, (3) skipped entry count equals the number of malformed entries provided.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test verifies error handling robustness with deterministic cases; no concurrency or volume testing needed at Unit level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Handle a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is about throughput and performance under load—testing requires volume and timing constraints that cannot be expressed at Unit level. Real failures (processing too slowly, buffer overflow, entries dropped, backlog accumulation) are only revealed when the full pipeline processes high-frequency data. Unit tests cannot measure throughput. Integration-level load testing (wiring data source → processing → output with synthetic high-volume data) can catch whether the system meets the throughput requirement.","test_description":"Generate 10,000 synthetic log entries and feed them to the ingestion and processing pipeline at a controlled rate of 10,000 per second (or inject them in rapid succession to simulate a burst). Measure: (1) total entries output/processed, (2) processing latency per batch, (3) any gaps or skipped entry numbers. Verify all 10,000 entries are successfully processed, none are dropped, and the system does not fall behind (output rate matches input rate within acceptable latency bounds).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"This is a load test of the full pipeline, which is necessary to reveal throughput bottlenecks. A Unit test cannot measure whether 10,000 entries/second is achievable.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.35,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13303,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13303},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64e1a10a-a7ab-4fdd-b4dc-ce257dd17f43","uuid":"8507521c-eabe-4dc0-989a-b5026a3df709"}
